quran[30]{c,v,t}:
  67,1,"Blessed is He in Whose Hand is the dominion of the Universe, and Who has power over everything;",footnotes:182186:1|182187:2|182188:3
  67,2,"Who created death and life that He might try you as to which of you is better in deed. He is the Most Mighty, the Most Forgiving;",footnotes:182189:1|182190:2
  67,3,"Who created the seven heavens one upon another. You will see no incongruity in the Merciful One's creation. Turn your vision again, can you see any flaw?",footnotes:182191:1|182192:2|182193:3
  67,4,"Then turn your vision again, and then again; in the end your vision will come back to you, worn out and frustrated."
  67,5,"We have adorned the lower heaven with lamps, and have made them a means to drive away the satans. We have prepared for them the chastisement of the Blazing Fire.",footnotes:182194:1|182195:2|182196:3
  67,6,"The chastisement of Hell awaits those who disbelieve in their Lord. What a wretched destination!",footnotes:182197:1
  67,7,"When they will be cast into it, they will hear it roar as it boils,",footnotes:182198:1
  67,8,"as though it will burst with rage. Every time a multitude is cast into it, its keepers will ask them: “Did no warner come to you?”",footnotes:182199:1
  67,9,"They will say: “Yes, a warner came to us, but we gave the lie to him and said: 'Allah has revealed nothing. You are surely in huge error.'",footnotes:182200:1
  67,10,"They will say: 'If we had only listened and understood, we would not be among the inmates of the Blazing Fire.'”",footnotes:182201:1
  67,11,"Thus will they confess their sins. Damned are these inmates of the Blazing Fire.",footnotes:182202:1
  67,12,"Surely forgiveness and a mighty reward await those who fear Allah without seeing Him.",footnotes:182203:1|182204:2
  67,13,"Whether you speak in secrecy or aloud, (it is all the same to Allah). He even knows the secrets that lie hidden in the breasts of people.",footnotes:182205:1
  67,14,"Would He not know, He Who has created, when He is All-Subtle, All-Aware?",footnotes:182206:1|182207:2
  67,15,"He it is Who made the earth subservient to you. So traverse in its tracks and partake of the sustenance He has provided. To Him will you be resurrected.",footnotes:182208:1|182209:2
  67,16,"Do you feel secure that He Who is in the heaven will not cause the earth to cave in with you, and then suddenly it will begin to rock violently?",footnotes:182210:1
  67,17,"Do you feel secure that He Who is in the heaven will not let loose upon you a storm of stones? Then shall you know what My warning is like!",footnotes:182211:1|182212:2
  67,18,"Those who came before them also gave the lie (to the Messengers): then how awesome was My chastisement!",footnotes:182213:1
  67,19,"Have they not seen birds above them spreading and closing their wings, with none holding them except the Merciful One? He oversees everything.",footnotes:182214:1|182215:2
  67,20,"Which is your army that will come to your aid against the Merciful Lord? But the unbelievers are in utter delusion.",footnotes:182216:1
  67,21,"Who shall provide for you if He withholds His sustenance? Nay; but they persist in rebellion and aversion."
  67,22,"Who is better guided: he who walks grovelling on his face, or he who walks upright on a Straight Path?",footnotes:182217:1
  67,23,"Say: “He it is Who has brought you into being, and has given you hearing and sight, and has given you hearts to think and understand. How seldom do you give thanks!”",footnotes:182218:1
  67,24,"Say: “Allah it is Who multiplied you in the earth and to Him you will be mustered.”",footnotes:182219:1
  67,25,"They say: “If you are truthful, tell us when will this promise (of the Hereafter) be fulfilled?”",footnotes:182220:1
  67,26,"Say: “Allah alone knows about that; and I am no more than a plain warner.”",footnotes:182221:1
  67,27,"When they will see it near at hand, the faces of all those who had denied it will be distraught, and then they will be told: “This is the doom which you used to ask for.”",footnotes:182222:1
  67,28,"Say to them: “Did you ever consider: whether Allah destroys me and those that are with me, or shows mercy to us, who can protect the unbelievers from a grievous chastisement?”",footnotes:182223:1
  67,29,"Say to them: “He is Merciful, and it is in Him that we believe, and it is in Him that we put all our trust. Soon will you know who is in manifest error.”",footnotes:182224:1
  67,30,"Say to them: “Did you even consider: if all the water that you have (in the wells) were to sink down into the depths of the earth, who will produce for you clear, flowing water?”",footnotes:182225:1
